'''Anunciado Serafini''' (November 16, 1898 – February 18, 1963) <ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bserafini.html|title=Bishop Anunciado Serafini [Catholic-Hierarchy]|first=David M.|last=Cheney|website=www.catholic-hierarchy.org|accessdate=27 November 2018}}</ref> was the [[Roman Catholic]] [[Bishop (Catholic Church)|bishop]] of what is now the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Mercedes-Luján]], [[Argentina]]. Ordained to the priesthood on December 20, 1924, Serafini was named Auxiliary Bishop of La Plata and Titular Bishop of Arycanda in 1935,<ref name="auto"/> and then Bishop of Mercedes in 1939.<ref name="auto"/>

On April 8, 1962, Bishop Serafini consecrated [[Antonio Quarracino]] to the episcopacy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bquar.html|title=Antonio Cardinal Quarracino [Catholic-Hierarchy]|first=David M.|last=Cheney|website=www.catholic-hierarchy.org|accessdate=27 November 2018}}</ref>  As Cardinal Quarracino later conducted the episcopal consecration of Jorge Mario Bergoglio, the future [[Pope Francis]], Bishop Serafini is part of that pope’s [[apostolic succession|episcopal lineage]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bbergj.html|title=Pope Francis (Jorge Mario Bergoglio) [Catholic-Hierarchy]|first=David M.|last=Cheney|website=www.catholic-hierarchy.org|accessdate=27 November 2018}}</ref>

