== In fiction == The Bishop of Sodor and Man is mentioned in the song "If you Want a Receipt for that Popular Mystery" sung by Colonel Calverley in the operetta ''[[Patience (opera)|Patience]]'' (1881) by [[W. S. Gilbert|Gilbert]] and [[Arthur Sullivan|Sullivan]]. The song lists the elements of a Heavy Dragoon, including "Style of the Bishop of Sodor and Man". The reference is to [[Rowley Hill (bishop)|Rowley Hill]] (Bishop 1877-1887).
The [[Sodor (fictional island)|Isle of Sodor (fictional island)]] is named after the diocese.
