{{Notability|date=October 2016}}
In [[Australian Aboriginal mythology]], '''Kondole''' was a mean and rude man.  One night, the performers during a ceremony needed someone to keep a fire going; Kondole was the only one with fire, and he hid in the bush.  The men argued with him, and one got frustrated and threw a [[spear]] into Kondole's [[human skull|skull]].  All the men then turned into [[animal]]s, including [[kangaroo]]s, [[Phalangeriformes|possums]], [[fish]] and [[bird]]s.  Kondole became a [[whale]] and the hole in his head from the spear became his [[blowhole (bio)|blowhole]]. The Kondole was the first whale according to Aboriginal myth.{{citation needed|date=April 2012}}
