'''Robin Alexis''' (born {{birth date and age|1955|03|31}} in [[New Hampshire]]{{sfn|Alexis|2008|p=5}}<ref name=PDN2010/><!--55 years old in July 2010-->) is a [[radio personality|radio]] and [[reality television]] personality, author, [[Reiki]] practitioner, and [[psychic]] from the state of [[Washington (state)|Washington]]. Her live call-in show ''Mystic Radio with Robin Alexis'' has been broadcast weekly since 2005,<!-- 2005 stated in Jason Havey interview, needs better source--> and as of 2017 is broadcast from [[KKNW]] in the [[Seattle]] market.<ref>{{citation |title=Program Guide: Mystic Radio |publisher=[[KKNW]] |url=http://1150kknw.com/show/mystic-radio/ |accessdate=November 26, 2016}}</ref> She appeared on the television program ''[[The Real L Word]]'' as a metaphysical mother,<ref name=PDN2010/> <!-- probably S1E7 August 1, 2010 --> which she describes as "speak[ing] to the souls of babies who haven't been conceived yet, who are in the womb, or are newborns...supporting parent's {{sic}} relationships with their yet unborn, lost, and aborted children".<ref>{{citation |title=Metaphysical mothering |work=Official website |author=Robin Alexis |url=http://robinalexis.com/content/metaphysical-mothering |accessdate=November 26, 2016}}</ref> Alexis gained note from press in the United States and from [[Merseyside Skeptics Society]] in the United Kingdom when she announced in 2010 that her metaphysical mothering included counseling a couple on hosting the reincarnation of [[Michael Jackson]].<ref name=PDN2010/><ref name=Luckutt2010/><ref name=merseysideskeptics/> She received a trademark on the term "metaphysical mothering" in 2011.<ref>{{citation |title=USPTO trademark notice: Metaphysical mothering |publisher=[[HighBeam]] {{subscription required}}|date=July 6, 2011|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-2391283081.html}}</ref>
She was a guest star on the third episode of ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live]]'' in 2003<!--Jan 28, 2003-->.<ref>{{citation|title=Jimmy Kimmel Live Season 1, Episode 3|website=[[TV.com]]|publisher=CBS Interactive|url=http://www.tv.com/shows/jimmy-kimmel-live/robin-alexis-228547/}}</ref><ref>{{citation|title= Kimmel's wit trumps snags|author=Josh Friedman|newspaper=The Los Angeles Times|date=January 31, 2003 |p=E.34|id=[[ProQuest]] article ID 421779928}}</ref>
