[[Abdulaziz Shamlan]], a Bahraini nationalist leader from the 1950s and later Bahrain's Ambassador in [[Cairo]], is one of the area's most famous ex-residents, along with the late Yousuf Abdulrahman Engineer whose house symbolizes tradition. Umm Al Hassam maintains its leftist traditions with the large headquarters for the [[National Democratic Action]] situated there.<ref>{{cite news|title=Residents picket Wa'ad meeting over BICI report|url=http://www.gulf-daily-news.com/NewsDetails.aspx?storyid=319421|accessdate=24 June 2012|newspaper=Gulf Daily News|date=11 December 2011}}</ref>
